This paper focuses on generating human face pictures using deep convolutional networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of optimization techniques to preserve the identity of the reference image, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of attribute-guided images, which is a common topic in multimedia (cs.MM) and graphics (cs.GR).
